{{Infobox organisation | former name = | bgcolor = <!-- header background color --> | fgcolor = <!-- header text color --> | image = File:National Film Archive of Thailand.jpg | image_border = | size = <!-- default 200px --> | alt = <!-- alt text; see [[WP:ALT]] --> | caption =National Film Archive of Thailand in Salaya | map = <!-- optional --> | msize = <!-- map size, optional, default 250px --> | malt = <!-- map alt text --> | mcaption = <!-- optional --> | map2 = | abbreviation = TFA | motto = | predecessor = | successor = | formation = 2009 <!-- {{Start date and age|df=yes|YYYY|MM|DD}} --> | extinction = <!-- date of extinction, optional --> | type = [[Film]], [[television]] [[charitable organisation]] | status = <!-- ad hoc, treaty, foundation, etc --> | purpose = <!-- focus as e.g. humanitarian, peacekeeping, etc --> | headquarters = | location = [[Phutthamonthon District|Phutthamonthon]], [[Nakhon Pathom Province|Nakhon Pathom]], Thailand | coords = <!-- Coordinates of location using a coordinates template --> | region_served = Thailand | membership = | language = Thai | general = <!-- Secretary General --> | leader_title = Director | leader_name = Dome Sukwong | leader_title2 = | leader_name2 = | leader_title3 = | leader_name3 = | leader_title4 = | leader_name4 = | key_people = | main_organ = <!-- gral. assembly, board of directors, etc --> | parent_organization = <!-- if one --> | affiliations = <!-- if any --> | budget = | num_staff = | num_volunteers = | website = {{URL|http://www.fapot.org}} | remarks = }}
The '''Film Archive (Public Organization)''' (TFA) is a [[film archive]] in [[Thailand]]. It was established in 1984 as the '''National Film Archive''', operating under the [[Fine Arts Department (Thailand)|Fine Arts Department]], [[Ministry of Culture (Thailand)|Ministry of Culture]].<ref>http://thaifilmjournal.blogspot.com.es/p/thai-film-archive.html</ref> It was reorganized into a [[public organization]] in 2009. It is in the [[Phutthamonthon District]] of [[Nakhon Pathom Province]].
